if you excel at a brain dead job what does that make you i have adhd and having a tough time focusing on my brain dead job thus i am not exceling anyone have some advice with respect to my position yes you must be challenged in order to reach your maximum potential but there is also something to be said for learning the ability to stick with a mundane job and make the most of a bad situation for a period of time we all must learn quickly that sometimes we must accept less than we want or need in order to prove to ourselves that we can thrive in an imperfect and ambiguous world life isn't about lamenting our current existence it's more about accepting our current lot in life and making the most out of it until we can grasp an opportunity to achieve at a higher level Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Mach kernel Adult attention-deficit disorder Learning disability Asperger syndrome Soul Methylphenidate Neurofeedback Second language acquisition Theory of conduct Action potential Autism Computer chess Strategic management Electrophysiology Poker jargon Leadership Procrastination Methamphetamine Unemployment Tri-Stat dX Economic inequality Doomsday argument Scientology beliefs and practices Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism Human brain Prime Minister of the United Kingdom Martial art Supply and demand Escape from New York Boss (video games) Comparing and contrasting Judaism and Christianity Son Goku (Dragon Ball) Affirmative action Hogwarts subjects Pole vault Abortion debate Grade (education) Where Mathematics Comes From Gifted Toronto Raptors Current teachings of Prem Rawat Parapsychology Clinical depression Law & Order Grand Theft Auto (game) Final Fantasy magic Grammatical aspect Esperanto as an international language MP3 Extreme Programming Workplace democracy Education in Singapore Numerology Alex Ferguson Computer Leather Blood (computer game) Artificial consciousness Education in the People's Republic of China Bible and reincarnation Graduate school Final